cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with speech enhancement, which is a subfield of audio processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) for speech enhancement, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a Modular Neural Network (MNN) that combines various DNNs specialized on different enhancement tasks, which is a machine learning approach. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses AutoEncoders (AEs) as an arbitrator to select the best module during run time, which is a type of neural network. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper deals with processing speech signals to enhance their quality, which is a subfield of signal processing.
